metadata.name: White Mountain Winter #135
metadata.description:
White Mountain Winter is collaboration between myself and the machine to describe scenes that are real, or were. Yet perhaps now foreign, or out of time, or far away. I provide the seed of a dream I remember, and trust the machine to help make it real again.

I grew up in a town much like some of these, homes dispersed throughout the valley beneath the shadows of the mountains rising around. This is a tribute to the memory of wintertime in that place; bleak, cold, grey, with the light seemingly always fading. Yet at the same time, the feeling of calm, solace, peace resonating through. Exposed to the mountain elements, yet protected by them. A delicate arrangement, but essential.

The seed of magic I remember is present in the experience of falling snow at dusk. Large flakes tumbling down and blanketing everything, no end in sight. The most striking thing is the silence. The fallen snow absorbing all distraction, insisting that your focus be sharpened to a singularity; right there, right then.

---
- Best rendered in Chrome browser (best performance, & canvas blur - please be patient :)
- Made with p5js
- Press "s" to save png

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #219
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: The dice is cast #23
metadata.description:
When I started studying the code and learning the "random" functions in early July 2022, it made me think of randomness when throwing dice. It is random, but with these restrictions (3 six-sided dice = 216 possibilities). 

With this mindset and theme, I began to create this first attempt at generative art. 

In my usual work, I take everyday objects, materials, etc. and play with them. For this series, I inserted blocks of polystyrene to give it substance. 

All the graphic elements, colours and random arrangements were created using P5.js. The photos of polystyrene and the dices are integrated.

Press ENTER to download as a jpg image. 

@Yomu Oyashi July 2022

metadata.name: Genesis FxHash by BanjoFunk #10
metadata.description:
Thanks to PureSpider and VectorRecite for helping me mint my 1st piece on FxHash!

This piece was inspired by Art Basel 2022 in Miami. Although haven't been that active in the Tezos space, was glad to be around the artists who keep this community genuine. 

The art in this piece is a combinations of colors and concepts that I have been exploring. Tezos has always inspired me to want to become a better artist. Style and individuality is hard to come by these days but I'm hoping that with healthy practice and execution that I could become a really good artist.

Always appreciative for any support and any "lack" of it will NOT stop me from supporting other artists in this space. Really wanted to get this piece out before the end of 2022 and I'm glad it's happening!

metadata.name: Gnarly #246
metadata.description:
Gnarly is an interactive nft game.

Fly across the city with your hoverboard and avoid the obstacles.

Each iteration will generate a totally different character to play!

Don't forget to collect the coins and eat pizza to recover your health!
You can also collect the sandclocks to slow down the time!

Use the touch/mouse or enter/space keys to jump (you can even double jump!)

Press S to save a screenshot of the game!
